{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 1. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
MattrMindr is a monolithic full-stack application with a clear client/server split. It is NOT a microservices architecture. The entire application runs from a single repository with two primary directories: a React frontend ("lextrack") and a Node.js/Express backend ("server"). Both share a single PostgreSQL database.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Request Flow:}\line
Browser \endash > React SPA (port 5000) \endash > CRA proxy \endash > Express API (port 3001) \endash > PostgreSQL\line
In production, Express serves the React build directly on port 5000 (no proxy needed).\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Key Architectural Decisions:}\line
\bullet  Single-page React app with no client-side routing library \endash  the entire UI is a state machine in one 21,000-line App.js file. Navigation is handled via a "currentView" state variable, not React Router.\line
\bullet  No ORM. All database access is raw SQL through the "pg" driver's parameterized queries.\line
\bullet  No migration framework. Schema changes are handled by a runtime migration system that runs ALTER TABLE IF NOT EXISTS statements at startup.\line
\bullet  Binary file storage uses a hybrid model: PostgreSQL BYTEA columns for most files, Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible) for large audio/video when configured.\line
\bullet  AI features use OpenAI's API (gpt-4o-mini primarily) and Google Gemini for OCR.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 2. TECHNOLOGY STACK & DEPENDENCIES\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 2.1 Frontend (lextrack/)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
\bullet  {\b React 19.2} via Create React App (react-scripts 5.0.1)\line
\bullet  {\b Tailwind CSS 3.4} for styling (PostCSS/Autoprefixer pipeline)\line
\bullet  {\b lucide-react} for icons throughout the UI\line
\bullet  No state management library \endash  all state is React useState/useEffect in App.js\line
\bullet  No routing library \endash  navigation via state variables\line
\bullet  CRA dev proxy configured in package.json: "proxy": "http://localhost:3001"\line
\bullet  {\b api.js} (\wave816 lines): thin fetch wrapper for every API call. Each function is a named export (e.g., apiGetCases, apiCreateTask). All calls go to relative URLs like "/api/cases" and include credentials: "include".\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 2.2 Backend (server/)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
\bullet  {\b Node.js 20} with {\b Express 4.19}\line
\bullet  {\b PostgreSQL} via "pg" driver (version 8.12)\line
\bullet  {\b express-session} with connect-pg-simple for session storage\line
\bullet  {\b bcryptjs} for password hashing\line
\bullet  {\b @google/generative-ai} for Gemini OCR pipeline\line
\bullet  {\b OpenAI SDK} (via Replit integration: AI_INTEGRATIONS_OPENAI_API_KEY + AI_INTEGRATIONS_OPENAI_BASE_URL)\line
\bullet  {\b @sendgrid/mail} for outbound email\line
\bullet  {\b twilio} (v5.12) for SMS\line
\bullet  {\b multer} for file upload handling\line
\bullet  {\b sharp} for image compression during OCR\line
\bullet  {\b pdf-parse} for native PDF text extraction\line
\bullet  {\b mammoth} for DOCX-to-HTML conversion\line
\bullet  {\b mailparser} for inbound email MIME parsing\line
\bullet  {\b otplib + qrcode} for TOTP-based MFA\line
\bullet  {\b @aws-sdk/client-s3} for Cloudflare R2 storage\line
\bullet  {\b jsonwebtoken} for external API JWT auth\line
\bullet  {\b docxtemplater + pizzip} for document template generation\line
\bullet  {\b xlsx} (SheetJS) for spreadsheet parsing\line
\bullet  {\b tesseract.js} for local OCR fallback\line
\bullet  {\b pdfkit} for PDF generation\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 2.3 System Dependencies\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
\bullet  {\b ffmpeg} (Nix package) \endash  required for Whisper audio transcription\line
\bullet  {\b pdftoppm} (poppler-utils) \endash  PDF page-to-image conversion for OCR pipeline\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

