{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 5. AUTHENTICATION & SESSION MANAGEMENT\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 5.1 Session Infrastructure\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Sessions are stored in PostgreSQL via connect-pg-simple in the "user_sessions" table. Cookie name is "lextrack.sid". Default session duration is 8 hours. In production, cookies are httpOnly + secure with sameSite=lax. The session stores: userId, userName, userEmail, userRole, userRoles.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 5.2 Firm Login Flow\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
1. User submits email + password to POST /api/auth/login\line
2. Server queries users table by email (case-insensitive)\line
3. Checks deleted_at for deactivated accounts\line
4. Compares bcrypt hash OR matches temp_password\line
5. If temp_password matches, it auto-hashes and sets must_change_password = true\line
6. If MFA enabled: stores mfaPendingUserId in session, returns \{requireMfa: true\}\line
7. If rememberMe=true: sets cookie maxAge to 30 days\line
8. On success: populates session with userId, userName, userEmail, userRole, userRoles\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 5.3 MFA (TOTP)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Uses otplib for TOTP secret generation and verification. QR codes generated via the qrcode library. Setup: POST /api/auth/mfa/setup generates secret + QR. Verification: user submits 6-digit code to /mfa/verify-setup to enable, or /mfa/verify during login. Stored in users.mfa_secret and users.mfa_enabled columns.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 5.4 Password Reset\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
POST /api/auth/forgot-password generates a random token, stores it in password_reset_token with 1-hour expiry, and sends email via SendGrid. POST /api/auth/reset-password validates token + email and updates password_hash.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 5.5 Three Auth Middleware\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
1. {\b requireAuth} (server/middleware/auth.js): Checks req.session.userId. Used for all firm API routes.\line
2. {\b requireClientAuth} (server/middleware/clientAuth.js): Checks req.session.clientId + req.session.isClient. Used for portal routes.\line
3. {\b requireExternalAuth} (server/middleware/external-auth.js): JWT Bearer token validation. Signed with EXTERNAL_JWT_SECRET. Populates req.extUser instead of session. Used for the /api/external routes.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 5.6 Client Portal Auth\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Completely separate from firm auth. Uses client_users table. Login via POST /api/portal/auth/login. Session sets isClient=true, clientId, clientCaseId. Critically sets userId=null to prevent portal users from accessing firm APIs.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 6. API ROUTE ARCHITECTURE\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
All routes are mounted in server/index.js. Every route file exports an Express Router. There are 60+ route files totaling \wave16,000 lines of backend code. Route mounting follows the pattern: app.use("/api/[resource]", routeModule).\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Key route files and their line counts (top 15):}\line
ai-agents.js: 1,188 lines \endash  11 AI agent endpoints\line
transcripts.js: 1,030 lines \endash  audio/video upload, Whisper transcription\line
case-documents.js: 735 lines \endash  document CRUD, folder management, OCR\line
templates.js: 685 lines \endash  document template generation (docxtemplater)\line
microsoft.js: 629 lines \endash  OAuth, Calendar, OneDrive integration\line
trial-center.js: 559 lines \endash  Trial Center CRUD\line
inbound-email.js: 531 lines \endash  Email webhook, filing auto-sort\line
medical-treatments.js: 527 lines \endash  Treatment CRUD + AI record parsing\line
trial-center-ai.js: 526 lines \endash  7 trial AI agents\line
collaborate.js: 514 lines \endash  Internal chat system\line
sms.js: 501 lines \endash  SMS config, send, AI draft, inbound webhook\line
cases.js: 433 lines \endash  Case CRUD + conflict check\line
task-flows.js: 428 lines \endash  Automation engine\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Standard CRUD Pattern:}\line
GET /api/[resource]?caseId=X \endash  list for a case\line
POST /api/[resource] \endash  create (body contains caseId + fields)\line
PUT /api/[resource]/:id \endash  update (partial update supported)\line
DELETE /api/[resource]/:id \endash  soft-delete (sets deleted_at) or hard-delete\line
All mutations log to case_activity via INSERT INTO case_activity.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 7. CASE MANAGEMENT CORE\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
Cases are the central entity. Every other table references cases via case_id.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Case Types:} Auto Accident, Truck Accident, Motorcycle Accident, Slip & Fall, Medical Malpractice, Product Liability, Wrongful Death, Workers' Compensation, Dog Bite, Premises Liability, Nursing Home Abuse, Other.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Case Stages:} Intake > Investigation > Treatment > Pre-Litigation Demand > Negotiation > Suit Filed > Discovery > Mediation > Trial Preparation > Trial > Settlement/Verdict > Closed.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Case Statuses:} Active, Pre-Litigation, In Litigation, Settled, Closed, Referred Out.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Staff Roles (14):} Managing Partner, Senior Partner, Partner, Associate Attorney, Of Counsel, Paralegal, Legal Assistant, Case Manager, Medical Records Coordinator, Intake Specialist, Office Administrator, IT Specialist, Investigator, App Admin.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Conflict Check:} When creating a case, the system searches existing cases and contacts by client name/email/phone for potential conflicts. Returns matching cases with party names.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b SOL Warning:} Red badge when statute of limitations is \u8804? 60 days away, amber when \u8804? 180 days. Displayed in case detail header and case list rows.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Litigation Toggle:} A header checkbox marks cases as "in litigation". When toggled on, auto-reassigns CM call tasks to Paralegal.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 8. PI-SPECIFIC DATA RELATIONSHIPS\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
The PI data model centers on the case entity with several domain tables:\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Insurance Tab Structure:}\line
case_insurance_policies (per case, multiple policies)\line
  \u8627? case_negotiations (per policy, linked via policy_id)\line
\line
Negotiations display nested under each insurance policy card. The UI calculates Gross Settlement (sum of demand amounts) and Net Settlement (gross minus liens and expenses).\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Medical Tab Structure:}\line
case_medical_treatments (per case, one per provider)\line
  \u8627? medical_records (per treatment, AI-parsed visit entries)\line
     \u8627? source_document_id -> case_documents(id)\line
\line
When a PDF is uploaded to a treatment, the AI parses it into individual visit entries with: provider, date, body part, procedures, pain levels, diagnoses, ICD codes, objective findings, referrals. These are staged for user review before committing.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Damages Tab Structure:}\line
case_damages (financial tracking per damage category)\line
  \u8627? Owed is auto-calculated: billed - reduction - insurance_paid - write_off\line
case_liens (lienholder claims against settlement)\line
  \u8627? Reduction supports both % and $ amounts\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 9. DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT PIPELINE\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 9.1 Upload Flow\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Documents go through: multer file parsing > size validation (25MB for docs, 100MB for filings via chunked upload) > text extraction > OCR if needed > database insert. File binary is stored in the file_data BYTEA column. For transcripts, large files can use R2 storage.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 9.2 OCR Pipeline (server/utils/extract-text.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Three-tier fallback OCR system:\line
1. {\b pdf-parse} (native text extraction) \endash  fastest, for digitally-created PDFs\line
2. If text yield is low (<200 chars or <20 words):\line
   a. {\b Gemini 3.1 Flash Lite Preview} \endash  sends PDF directly to Gemini API\line
   b. {\b Gemini 2.0 Flash} \endash  converts pages to JPEG via pdftoppm, compresses oversized images with sharp, sends to Gemini\line
3. {\b Tesseract.js} \endash  local fallback when API keys unavailable\line
\line
For PDFs, the extractTextWithPages() variant returns text with [PAGE N] markers for accurate citations in medical record parsing.\line
\line
For case_documents: PDFs trigger async OCR (ocr_status = "processing", background extraction updates to "complete" or "failed"). Non-PDFs do inline extraction.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 9.3 R2 Hybrid Storage (server/r2.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Uses @aws-sdk/client-s3 to connect to Cloudflare R2. Configured via R2_ACCOUNT_ID, R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID, R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, R2_BUCKET_NAME. Supports standard put/get/delete plus S3 multipart upload for large files. When R2 is configured, transcripts store r2_audio_key/r2_video_key instead of audio_data/video_data BYTEA. isR2Configured() acts as a feature flag.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 9.4 Document Viewer\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Frontend renders documents in floating draggable/resizable windows. Supports:\line
\bullet  PDF: iframe viewer\line
\bullet  DOCX/DOC: mammoth HTML conversion\line
\bullet  XLSX/XLS: SheetJS interactive table with sheet tabs\line
\bullet  PPTX: jszip XML parsing into slide cards\line
\bullet  Images: blob URL display\line
\bullet  Audio/Video: HTML5 media player\line
Multiple documents can be open simultaneously with independent z-ordering.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 10. AI AGENT SYSTEM\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 10.1 Architecture\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
All AI calls use the OpenAI SDK with credentials from Replit integration (AI_INTEGRATIONS_OPENAI_API_KEY + AI_INTEGRATIONS_OPENAI_BASE_URL). Every call includes store: false to prevent training on attorney-client privileged data. Primary model is gpt-4o-mini for cost efficiency.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 10.2 Built-in Agents (server/routes/ai-agents.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
11 agents, each with specialized system prompts:\line
1. {\b Liability Analysis} \endash  tort law, comparative negligence, state-specific rules\line
2. {\b Deadline Generator} \endash  SOL, discovery deadlines, jurisdiction-aware (returns JSON)\line
3. {\b Case Valuation & Strategy} \endash  case value estimate, litigation strategy\line
4. {\b Document Drafting} \endash  demand letters, motions, correspondence\line
5. {\b Case Triage} \endash  ranks cases by SOL proximity, value, treatment status (returns JSON)\line
6. {\b Client Communication Summary} \endash  treatment status, claim progress\line
7. {\b Medical Record Summarizer} \endash  focuses on medical/accident/expert reports\line
8. {\b Task Suggestions} \endash  PI-specific task recommendations (returns JSON)\line
9. {\b Filing Classifier} \endash  classifies filing types (returns JSON)\line
10. {\b Advocate AI} \endash  conversational assistant with case context\line
11. {\b Batch Case Manager} \endash  bulk operations via natural language\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 10.3 Context Building\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Each agent dynamically fetches relevant data from the database. For example, Case Strategy fetches notes, tasks, deadlines, insurance policies, medical treatments, damages, liens, and negotiations via Promise.all. This data is serialized into the user message or system prompt.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 10.4 AI Training Layer\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
The ai_training table stores user-defined training entries (office guidelines, preferences) that get appended to system prompts (up to 8,000 chars). Function: getTrainingContext(agentType, userId).\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 10.5 AI Search (server/routes/ai-search.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Full-caseload synthesis search. Queries EVERY table in the database, builds dense text summaries for each case, then passes all summaries + user query to gpt-4o. The AI returns relevant case IDs with match reasons. Document/transcript filenames are weighted 2x in relevance scoring. No vector database or embeddings used.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 10.6 Custom Agents (server/routes/custom-agents-builder.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Users can create custom AI agents with:\line
\bullet  Model selection: gpt-4o, gpt-4o-mini, claude-3.5-sonnet, gemini-2.0-flash\line
\bullet  Custom system prompt + optional instruction file upload\line
\bullet  Configurable context sources: notes, filings, documents, medical_records\line
\bullet  Run mode (single execution) or Chat mode (conversational)\line
\bullet  Private or shared visibility\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 10.7 Formatting Rules\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
A NO_MARKDOWN constant is appended to all non-JSON prompts. It instructs the AI to use ALL CAPS for headings and plain text instead of Markdown formatting, ensuring clean display in the UI.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 11. MICROSOFT 365 INTEGRATION\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 11.1 OAuth Flow\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Uses Microsoft Identity Platform v2.0 Authorization Code Flow. Config stored in integration_configs table (clientId, clientSecret, redirectUri). Scopes: openid, profile, email, Files.ReadWrite.All, Calendars.ReadWrite, Contacts.ReadWrite, offline_access. Tokens stored per-user in users table columns. getValidToken(userId) handles automatic refresh.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 11.2 Calendar Sync\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
\bullet  Manual push: POST /api/microsoft/calendar/push-deadline creates/updates Outlook event\line
\bullet  Auto sync: When users enable ms_calendar_sync, deadline create/update in deadlines.js auto-pushes to Outlook\line
\bullet  Type filtering: ms_sync_deadline_types (JSONB array) controls which deadline types sync. Empty array = all types\line
\bullet  Delete sync: Deleting a deadline also removes its Outlook event via deleteOutlookEvent\line
\bullet  Two-way display: GET /api/microsoft/calendar/events fetches Outlook events for calendar view\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 11.3 OneDrive Import\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
\bullet  POST /api/microsoft/onedrive/resolve-link: Encodes share URL to base64url shareId, calls Graph /shares/\{shareId\}/driveItem. Supports files and folders.\line
\bullet  POST /api/microsoft/onedrive/import-file: Downloads file via Graph API, runs OCR pipeline, inserts into case_documents with source="OneDrive". 25MB limit. Folder validation. Async OCR for PDFs.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 12. EMAIL & SMS PROCESSING\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 12.1 Inbound Email (server/routes/inbound-email.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
SendGrid Inbound Parse webhook at POST /api/inbound-email. Two routing branches:\line
\line
{\b Branch 1 \endash  filings@:}\line
Extracts court case number from subject line via regex. Matches against cases.court_case_number. On match: saves correspondence, extracts PDF attachments, runs AI classification (filing type, party, dates), creates deadline entries for hearing dates. On no match: stores in unmatched_filings_emails table.\line
\line
{\b Branch 2 \endash  case-[ID]@:}\line
Links directly to case by ID. Saves to case_correspondence. Triage logic:\line
\bullet  PDFs with "ALAFILE E-NOTICE" markers go to case_filings\line
\bullet  Audio files with "voice message" subject go to case_voicemails\line
\bullet  Other audio goes to case_transcripts (triggers auto-transcription)\line
\bullet  Other attachments go to case_documents\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 12.2 SMS System\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Outbound:} POST /api/sms/send formats number to E.164, sends via Twilio, logs to sms_messages.\line
{\b AI Drafting:} POST /api/sms/draft generates professional 160-char reminder using gpt-4o-mini.\line
{\b Scheduled:} sms_scheduler.js generates reminders from sms_configs. Checks upcoming hearings, deadlines, meetings. Creates "pending" entries in sms_scheduled. Background worker sends at scheduled time.\line
{\b Inbound Webhook:} POST /api/sms/inbound receives Twilio webhook. Matches incoming number against: previous outbound messages, sms_configs, sms_watch_numbers. Unmatched messages stored with case_id = NULL.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 13. TRIAL CENTER\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
Full trial preparation module with 10 tabs: Witnesses, Exhibits, Jury, Motions, Outlines, Jury Instructions, Demonstratives, Quick Docs, Trial Log, AI Agents.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Civil PI context:} Uses plaintiff/client terminology. Civil jury options (6-12 jurors). PI-relevant motion types. Witness types include treating physicians, expert witnesses, accident reconstructionists.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b 7 Trial AI Agents:} Witness preparation (cross-exam, credibility attacks), jury selection analysis, opening/closing statement drafting, objection analysis, trial strategy, exhibit analysis, Daubert challenge evaluation.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Voir Dire Integration:} Imports juror data from external VoirDire.MattrMindr.com service. Brings demographics, bias ratings, and AI analysis into trial_jurors table.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 14. CLIENT PORTAL\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
Separate SPA at /portal (lextrack/src/portal/PortalApp.js). Completely isolated auth system.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Invite Flow:} Firm staff invite clients from case detail "Client Portal" tab. System generates temp password, optionally sends welcome email via SendGrid. Client logs in with email + password.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Visibility Controls:} Per-case settings (client_portal_settings table) let firms toggle what clients can see: stage progress, attorney name, case type, accident date, court date, documents, messaging, medical treatments, negotiations, case value. Plus a custom status message.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Portal Features:}\line
\bullet  Case progress timeline (PI stages mapped to client-friendly labels)\line
\bullet  Case info cards (filtered by visibility)\line
\bullet  Messaging (bidirectional chat via client_messages table)\line
\bullet  Document upload (marked with source="client") + view firm-shared docs\line
\bullet  "What to Expect" section explaining the PI process\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 15. CUSTOM AUTOMATION ENGINE\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 15.1 Task Flows\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Automated task creation based on case events. A flow has a trigger_condition (JSONB with field/operator/value rules) and trigger_on setting (create/update/both).\line
\line
{\b Trigger fields:} status, stage, caseType, inLitigation, clientBankruptcy, stateJurisdiction, county, dispositionType, injuryType.\line
{\b Operators:} equals, not_equals, contains, is_true, is_false, changed_to.\line
\line
Each flow has ordered steps with their own conditions:\line
\bullet  prior_step \endash  another step must have been created first\line
\bullet  case_field \endash  case field must match condition\line
\bullet  task_status \endash  existing task must be in specified status\line
\bullet  role_assigned \endash  specific role must be filled on case\line
\bullet  case_age \endash  case must be X days old\line
\bullet  has_document \endash  document matching pattern must exist\line
\bullet  priority_level \endash  open task count at priority level meets threshold\line
\line
Execution is tracked in task_flow_executions to prevent duplicates. evaluateFlowsForCase() is called from cases.js POST and PUT endpoints.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 15.2 Custom Dashboard Widgets\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
User-defined widgets: Metric (count/sum/average), List (filtered records), Chart (bar/pie). Data sources: cases, tasks, deadlines, contacts, correspondence, expenses, staff_assigned. Each widget has JSONB config for filters (field/operator/value). Widgets can be private or public.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 15.3 Custom Reports\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
SQL-based report builder with AI-assisted configuration. Reports define a data source and JSONB config for columns, filters, grouping, and sorting. Supports CSV export.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 16. REAL-TIME CHAT (COLLABORATE)\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
Internal messaging system in server/routes/collaborate.js (\wave514 lines). Uses polling-based approach (NOT WebSocket). Tables: chat_channels, chat_channel_members, chat_groups, chat_messages, chat_typing.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
Features: Direct messages, group chats, channel-based conversations, @mentions (stored as INT[] of user IDs), file attachments, typing indicators (chat_typing table with timestamp-based expiry), message threading.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 17. DEPLOYMENT & PRODUCTION\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
{\b Deployment Target:} Replit Autoscale (stateless, scales on traffic).\line
{\b Build Command:} npm install && cd server && npm install && cd ../lextrack && npm install && CI=false npm run build\line
{\b Run Command:} NODE_ENV=production node server/index.js\line
\line
In production:\line
\bullet  Express serves React build from lextrack/build/ on port 5000\line
\bullet  trust proxy is enabled (app.set("trust proxy", 1))\line
\bullet  Session cookies are secure + httpOnly + sameSite=lax\line
\bullet  CORS origin is empty (same-origin since Express serves frontend)\line
\bullet  SMS scheduler runs every 60s (vs 300s in dev)\line
\bullet  PostgreSQL SSL enabled with rejectUnauthorized: false\line
\bullet  CI=false in build command prevents ESLint warnings from failing the build\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 18. RUNTIME MIGRATION SYSTEM\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
The ensureColumns() function in server/index.js runs at startup, before app.listen(). It executes three categories of DDL:\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
1. {\b Table creations:} CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS for transcript_history, custom_reports, custom_agents, permissions, unmatched_filings_emails, custom_task_flows, custom_task_flow_steps, task_flow_executions, custom_dashboard_widgets, integration_configs.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
2. {\b Column migrations:} ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS for 40+ columns across users, cases, case_transcripts, case_documents, case_damages, case_liens, case_negotiations, tasks, deadlines, jury_analyses, sms_messages, medical_records, document_folders, custom_task_flow_steps.\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
3. {\b Data fixes:} Retroactive voicemail detection (updates case_correspondence where subject matches "voice message" pattern). Admin user seeding (creates admin@mattrmindr.com if not exists).\par}

{\pard\sb100\sa100\f0\fs22\cf1
All migration statements use .catch(() => \{\}) to silently ignore errors (column already exists, table already exists). This makes the system idempotent.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 19. EXTERNAL INTEGRATIONS\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 19.1 MattrMindr Scribe (server/routes/scribe.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Audio transcription service. Users connect via Scribe credentials (stored in users table: scribe_url, scribe_token, scribe_user_email). Workflow: send audio to Scribe via temporary download token > Scribe processes > app polls for status > imports transcript segments + AI summaries into case_transcripts table.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 19.2 Voir Dire Analyst (server/routes/voirdire.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Juror analysis service at voirdire.mattrmindr.com. Imports juror data (demographics, bias ratings, AI analysis) into trial_jurors table. Connected via user credentials in users table.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 19.3 External API (server/routes/external.js)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
JWT-authenticated REST API for third-party access. Uses Bearer token with EXTERNAL_JWT_SECRET. CORS configured via EXTERNAL_CORS_ORIGINS env var. Mounted at /api/external with separate CORS middleware.\par}

{\pard\sb0\sa0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\cf3\par}

{\pard\sb600\sa200\keepn\f2\fs36\b\cf2 20. SECURITY & PERMISSIONS\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 20.1 Password Security\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
bcryptjs with salt rounds = 10. Temporary passwords for new users sent via SendGrid. Password reset tokens with 1-hour expiry. Optional MFA via TOTP (otplib).\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 20.2 SQL Injection Prevention\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
All database queries use pg's parameterized queries ($1, $2, ...). No string interpolation of user input into SQL.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 20.3 Role-Based Access\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Checked at the route level by inspecting req.session.userRole or req.session.userRoles. Admin operations (send temp password, manage permissions, customization) require "App Admin" role. Batch delete requires attorney-level roles (Managing Partner through Associate Attorney).\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 20.4 Granular Permissions (permissions table)\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Supports both role-based and user-based permissions. Permission keys define access rights. target_type is "role" or "user". Supports optional expiration dates. CRUD via /api/permissions.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 20.5 Confidential Cases\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Cases with confidential=true are only visible to directly assigned staff (lead_attorney, second_attorney, case_manager, paralegal, investigator) and App Admin users.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 20.6 Soft Delete & Data Recovery\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Most records use soft-delete (deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ). The Deleted Data view (/api/deleted-data) allows searching, batch restore, and batch purge of deleted records. Auto-purge runs daily for records older than the configured retention period.\par}

{\pard\sb200\sa100\keepn\f0\fs26\b\cf2 20.7 OpenAI Privacy\par}
{\pard\li360\f0\fs22\cf1
Every OpenAI API call includes store: false to prevent attorney-client privileged data from being used for model training.\par}

